<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 01 at 2:36AM EST  by NWS New York City - Upton</headline>
<description>Areas of fog, locally dense, will affect portions of southern
Connecticut overnight. Visibilities will generally run 1/2 to 1
mile, with some areas down to 1/4 mile or less at times.
If driving, be prepared for changeable and suddenly reduced
visibilities. Proceed with extra caution, drive slowly and allow
for extra space between vehicles. Also, use low beam headlights.</description>
